page.title: 09TUDOR HOUSE
page.content: TUDOR HOUSE IS PROBALY THE OLDEST HOUSE IN THE ROW,A FRIEND OF OUR SCHOOL LIVES IN THIS HOUSE.THE HOUSE DATES BACK TO 1746.THE GARAGE WAS ONCE A COTTAGE.THE DOOR FRAME IS STILL THE SAME ONE AS WENT IN WHEN IT WAS BUILT.WHEN YOU WALK IN THOUGH THE FRONT DOOR YOU CAN SEE PART OF THE CRUCK WHICH WHEN GOES THOUGH AND OVER TO THE CEILING OF THE STAIR-CASE AND ENDS UP IN THE BEDROOM.YOU CANNOT SEE THE OTHER SIDE OF THE CRUCK BECAUSE IT HAS BEEN PLASTERED IN.YOU CAN STILL SEE THE SAME CHIMNEY BREAST IN THE BEDROOM AS-WELL.
